  "text": "Ang II, mtROS, and HIF-1 Vol. 21, September 15, 2010 to demonstrate here that mitochondrial/complex III-generated mtROS are indispensable for HIF-1 activation by Ang II. It is important to note that the NADPH oxidase and the mitochondria are not the only ROS-generating systems in VSMCs [CITATION_1] . It is possible that the activity of other oxidases and ROS generators may affect HIF-1 activation at different levels. Continued studies in this area will clarify the role of other oxidases and ROS generators on HIF-1 activation in nonhypoxic conditions.",
